By BO Staff Writer The following statement was previously published on the Black First Land First website: On 30 November 2019 Black First Land First (BLF) held a Special Policy Conference (SPC) in Durban, KwaZulu-Natal to find a way forward for the movement which had been deregistered – at the instance of the racist whites only Freedom Front Plus (FF+) – by the Independent Electoral Commission (IEC). The full address, delivered at the SPC by the President of BLF Andile Mngxitama, can be accessed via the link, http://blf.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BLF-Special-Policy-Conference-Address-President-F.pdf No related posts.